            {
              "id": 906995,
              "key": "74fb4982-9e51-4f88-8189-0449989328a7",
              "title": "Pro Tips on Using the ELK Stack",
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "### Pro Tips on Using the ELK Stack\n**The ELK stack requires more memory than everything else in this course.**\n- The standard config recommends 2GB. This is why we migrate to a larger instance. \n- It may also be necessary to stop anything else that you have set up in this course (i.e. Jenkins, Prometheus, and Grafana). \n- If the Ansible installation script for Elasticsearch takes too long (more than 5 minutes for a single item) you may have run out of memory.\n- Do not be alarmed, just restart the EC2 instance either through the command line, or if necessary in the AWS web console.",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            },
            {
